      "solution": "H, W = map(int, input().split())\ngrid = [list(map(int, input().split())) for _ in range(H)]\nR, C = map(int, input().split())\n\ntotal = 0\ndirections = [(-1, 0), (1, 0), (0, -1), (0, 1)]\n\nfor dr, dc in directions:\n    nr, nc = R + dr, C + dc\n    if 0 <= nr < H and 0 <= nc < W:\n        total += grid[nr][nc]\n\nprint(total)",
